<zk xmlns="http://www.zkoss.org/2005/zul"
	xmlns:h="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
	xmlns:n="http://www.zkoss.org/2005/zk/native"
	xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" 
	xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.zkoss.org/2005/zul http://www.zkoss.org/2005/zul/zul.xsd">
<n:p>Test the spinner with draggable=&quot;true&quot;, which is between -10~10 and each step is 2.</n:p>
<vbox>
<label>When the Draggable has been set true;</label>
<label>Click the up and down arrow rapidly and continuously, there will be a phantom spinner show up right next to mouse pointer!</label>
<label>(that's user's manipulation issue, not a bug.)</label>
</vbox>

<window title="Spinner test" border="normal" width="200px">
<spinner id="sp" />
<zscript><![CDATA[
                  
                  sp.setValue(new Integer(1));
                  sp.setStep(2);
                  sp.setConstraint("min -10 max 10");
                  sp.setDraggable("true");
                  ]]></zscript>

<vbox>
<separator />
<label>draggable:</label>
<radiogroup onCheck="sp.draggable = self.selectedItem.label">
<radio label="true" selected="true"/>
<radio label="false"/>
</radiogroup>
</vbox>
</window>
</zk>